   conclusions and notes:


   Coyotes are everywhere on the study site, occupied sites near 1.0 (excep 2019 ~.6)


   no strong correlation with habitat covariates, across elevation, slope, aspect, vegetation, snow, and productivity


   No strong prey relationships on the study site, moderate correlation with chipmonk sp


   lack of associations may reflect generalist nature of coyotes living at upper elevations of SN
